This project is developed using the following stack:

    Frontend: Next.js with TypeScript
    Backend: Python (Django) with Django Rest Framework

Getting Started

To start the project, please ensure that Docker and Docker Compose are installed on your system.

If you haven't installed Docker and Docker Compose yet, you can download and install them from the official Docker website:

    Docker: https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/
    Docker Compose: https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/

Once Docker and Docker Compose are installed, follow these steps:

    Clone the repository to your local machine.
    Navigate to the project directory.
    Run make up command to start the project.

Dockerization

The entire project is dockerized, utilizing two different Docker Compose files:

    Backend: Docker Compose file for the Django backend.
    Frontend: Docker Compose file for the Next.js frontend.

Both docker compose file will be started with the "make up" command from the project's root folder